> You only have to think of traditional Sunday roasts to know that lamb and mint is a match made in herb heaven. We're bringing a Middle Eastern twist to this classic combination with these minted meatballs. Enjoy!

Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked and finely chopped) leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks). Roughly chop the @dried apricots{40%g}(roughly chopped). Trim the tops from the @green beans{150%g}(tops trimmed). Zest and juice the @lemon{1/2}(zested and juiced).

Put the @lamb mince{200%g} in a #mixing bowl{} with half the shallot, half the mint, the dried apricots and the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and some @pepper{} (to taste), then mix together with your hands until well combined. Shape into four meatballs per person. Set aside.

> Important: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a #large saucepan{} with half the @chicken stock powder{1/2} and bring to the boil. When boiling, stir in the @couscous{150%g}, pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium heat and add the remaining shallot. Cook, stirring, until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Stir in half the garlic, the @dried thyme{1/2} and the @cumin seeds{1/2%tsp}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @chopped tomatoes{1}(diced) and add the remaining stock pot. Stir to dissolve, add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{} (to taste), then simmer the sauce until thick and tomatoey, ~{7-10%minutes}.

Whilst the sauce is simmering, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the meatballs. Cook until brown on the outside (turning frequently), ~{6-7%minutes}. Once the meatballs are browned, add them to the sauce and simmer for ~{5-6%minutes}. Wipe out the meatball pan with #kitchen paper{}.

> Important: The meatballs are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Put the now empty frying pan back on medium heat and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the green beans. Stir-fry until soft, ~{6-7%minutes}. Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{} and stir in the remaining mint. Add some lemon zest and juice to taste. Spoon the couscous into #bowls{}, top with the meatballs and serve with the green beans on the side. Tuck in!